{"_env":"NODEJS","_serializationMethod":"normal","_autosave":false,"_autosaveInterval":5000,"_collections":[{"name":"items","unindexedSortComparator":"js","defaultLokiOperatorPackage":"js","_dynamicViews":[],"uniqueNames":[],"transforms":{},"rangedIndexes":{},"_data":[{"slug":"back-to-basics","title":"Back to Basics","date":"2021-10-26T16:22:40.000Z","toc":[],"body":{"type":"root","children":[{"type":"element","tag":"p","props":{},"children":[{"type":"text","value":"Apologies for the swearing and fuck it, here goes..."}]},{"type":"text","value":"\n"},{"type":"element","tag":"p","props":{},"children":[{"type":"text","value":"As I write this, I have seven websites deployed on Netlify. I have another two or three hosted on GitHub Pages. And a number of these also have DNS records pointing my own custom domains in their direction. Many of them are blogs; in fact, seven of them are blogs. One of them is also supposed to be a portfolio website, but it's in an unfinished state. And the others are either documentation websites or demos. And the issue is this... That's too much; that's more than I can chew. Actually, this was a really good idea until it wasn't. I deliberately separated out my work into multiple domains in order to prove that a general framework which all of them use was fit for purpose. After quite a lot of tweaking... it is. At least, I think it is; there will always be extra kinks that need working out. Anyways, more than I can chew..."}]},{"type":"text","value":"\n"},{"type":"element","tag":"p","props":{},"children":[{"type":"text","value":"I don't wanna maintain all of that. I "},{"type":"element","tag":"strong","props":{},"children":[{"type":"text","value":"do"}]},{"type":"text","value":" want to write across several different topics, and I "},{"type":"element","tag":"strong","props":{},"children":[{"type":"text","value":"do"}]},{"type":"text","value":" want to separate those out into different domains but... "},{"type":"element","tag":"em","props":{},"children":[{"type":"text","value":"eventually"}]},{"type":"text","value":". I want to do that "},{"type":"element","tag":"em","props":{},"children":[{"type":"text","value":"eventually"}]},{"type":"text","value":". We're putting the cart before the horse here, to use a second cliché. I do know full well that the different topics I think I may want to write about won't appeal to everybody, hence the separation of scopes, but... I don't exactly have an audience to begin with; why worry about alienating an audience of zero - readers are already an alien concept here. So I'm dragging myself back to basics... Back to "},{"type":"element","tag":"strong","props":{},"children":[{"type":"text","value":"one"}]},{"type":"text","value":" website, one source from which I publish anything I want. Code, politics, philosophy, writing; all of it under one roof... for now. We'll worry about what that means later, we'll talk about personal brands and per-project branding and blah-blah-blah "},{"type":"element","tag":"em","props":{},"children":[{"type":"text","value":"later"}]},{"type":"text","value":"."}]},{"type":"text","value":"\n"},{"type":"element","tag":"p","props":{},"children":[{"type":"text","value":"The truth is I have a lot on my plate. And a lot more that I want to heap onto it..."}]},{"type":"text","value":"\n"},{"type":"element","tag":"p","props":{},"children":[{"type":"element","tag":"strong","props":{},"children":[{"type":"text","value":"I am..."}]},{"type":"text","value":" a professional software developer working with several clients."}]},{"type":"text","value":"\n"},{"type":"element","tag":"p","props":{},"children":[{"type":"element","tag":"strong","props":{},"children":[{"type":"text","value":"I am..."}]},{"type":"text","value":" a father to a four year old on the autism spectrum."}]},{"type":"text","value":"\n"},{"type":"element","tag":"p","props":{},"children":[{"type":"element","tag":"strong","props":{},"children":[{"type":"text","value":"I am..."}]},{"type":"text","value":" still trying to also enjoy games, film and other media I love."}]},{"type":"text","value":"\n"},{"type":"element","tag":"p","props":{},"children":[{"type":"element","tag":"strong","props":{},"children":[{"type":"text","value":"I want to..."}]},{"type":"text","value":" write several works of fiction."}]},{"type":"text","value":"\n"},{"type":"element","tag":"p","props":{},"children":[{"type":"element","tag":"strong","props":{},"children":[{"type":"text","value":"I want to..."}]},{"type":"text","value":" publish and manage my own software platforms."}]},{"type":"text","value":"\n"},{"type":"element","tag":"p","props":{},"children":[{"type":"element","tag":"strong","props":{},"children":[{"type":"text","value":"I want to..."}]},{"type":"text","value":" produce a few video games."}]},{"type":"text","value":"\n"},{"type":"element","tag":"p","props":{},"children":[{"type":"text","value":"There's a lot here to think about, a lot here to manage, and I am barely scratching the surface. Life... is pretty fucking complicated. So let's simplify."}]},{"type":"text","value":"\n"},{"type":"element","tag":"p","props":{},"children":[{"type":"text","value":"I intend to remove the six other websites hosted on Netlify, with the exception of this one - "},{"type":"element","tag":"em","props":{},"children":[{"type":"text","value":"thombruce.com"}]},{"type":"text","value":". I intend to move all of my blogging to this domain, including those old articles. This will break hyperlinks I've shared previously, but I don't care (they don't get a lot of traffic anyway; it doesn't effect me much). Then I intend to work the problems I have, one by one or as necessary and just... get it done. Priority numero uno is always my four year old, turning five soon, then I have to apportion time to everything else... one by one... until they're done."}]},{"type":"text","value":"\n"},{"type":"element","tag":"p","props":{},"children":[{"type":"text","value":"Step one: Rebuild thombruce.com to host its own blog content and transfer the rest of my content to it."}]},{"type":"text","value":"\n"},{"type":"element","tag":"p","props":{},"children":[{"type":"text","value":"Reconvene when that is done."}]}]},"text":"\nApologies for the swearing and fuck it, here goes...\n\nAs I write this, I have seven websites deployed on Netlify. I have another two or three hosted on GitHub Pages. And a number of these also have DNS records pointing my own custom domains in their direction. Many of them are blogs; in fact, seven of them are blogs. One of them is also supposed to be a portfolio website, but it's in an unfinished state. And the others are either documentation websites or demos. And the issue is this... That's too much; that's more than I can chew. Actually, this was a really good idea until it wasn't. I deliberately separated out my work into multiple domains in order to prove that a general framework which all of them use was fit for purpose. After quite a lot of tweaking... it is. At least, I think it is; there will always be extra kinks that need working out. Anyways, more than I can chew...\n\nI don't wanna maintain all of that. I **do** want to write across several different topics, and I **do** want to separate those out into different domains but... _eventually_. I want to do that _eventually_. We're putting the cart before the horse here, to use a second cliché. I do know full well that the different topics I think I may want to write about won't appeal to everybody, hence the separation of scopes, but... I don't exactly have an audience to begin with; why worry about alienating an audience of zero - readers are already an alien concept here. So I'm dragging myself back to basics... Back to **one** website, one source from which I publish anything I want. Code, politics, philosophy, writing; all of it under one roof... for now. We'll worry about what that means later, we'll talk about personal brands and per-project branding and blah-blah-blah _later_.\n\nThe truth is I have a lot on my plate. And a lot more that I want to heap onto it...\n\n**I am...** a professional software developer working with several clients.\n\n**I am...** a father to a four year old on the autism spectrum.\n\n**I am...** still trying to also enjoy games, film and other media I love.\n\n**I want to...** write several works of fiction.\n\n**I want to...** publish and manage my own software platforms.\n\n**I want to...** produce a few video games.\n\nThere's a lot here to think about, a lot here to manage, and I am barely scratching the surface. Life... is pretty fucking complicated. So let's simplify.\n\nI intend to remove the six other websites hosted on Netlify, with the exception of this one - _thombruce.com_. I intend to move all of my blogging to this domain, including those old articles. This will break hyperlinks I've shared previously, but I don't care (they don't get a lot of traffic anyway; it doesn't effect me much). Then I intend to work the problems I have, one by one or as necessary and just... get it done. Priority numero uno is always my four year old, turning five soon, then I have to apportion time to everything else... one by one... until they're done.\n\nStep one: Rebuild thombruce.com to host its own blog content and transfer the rest of my content to it.\n\nReconvene when that is done.\n","dir":"/blog","path":"/blog/back-to-basics","extension":".md","createdAt":"2021-10-26T16:40:52.561Z","updatedAt":"2021-10-26T16:40:52.561Z","meta":{"version":0,"revision":0,"created":1635266544483},"$loki":1}],"idIndex":[1],"maxId":1,"_dirty":true,"_nestedProperties":[],"transactional":false,"asyncListeners":false,"disableMeta":false,"disableChangesApi":true,"disableDeltaChangesApi":true,"cloneObjects":false,"cloneMethod":"deep","changes":[],"_fullTextSearch":{"ii":{"title":{"_store":true,"_optimizeChanges":true,"docCount":1,"docStore":[[0,{"fieldLength":3}]],"totalFieldLength":3,"root":{"k":[98,116],"v":[{"k":[97],"v":[{"k":[99,115],"v":[